HEADWORD: Evil-eyed
<hw>E"vil-eyed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>a.</pos> <def>Possessed of the
supposed evil eye; also, looking with envy, jealousy, or bad design;
malicious.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

